            <title>[WFLY-7718] It is possible to set max-concurrent-requests attribute of request limit filter in undertow to value lower than one</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-7718</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;According to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/undertow-io/undertow/blob/master/core/src/main/java/io/undertow/server/handlers/RequestLimitingHandler.java#L64&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/undertow-io/undertow/blob/master/core/src/main/java/io/undertow/server/handlers/RequestLimitingHandler.java#L64&lt;/a&gt; it should not be possible to perform this operation: &lt;tt&gt;/subsystem=undertow/configuration=filter/request-limit=foo:add(max-concurrent-requests=-42)&lt;/tt&gt; so it looks like no value check is performed in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
